3.8.3 Chop command
------------------

Chop (or split) files at design unit.

     $ ghdl --chop FILES

   `GHDL' reads files, and writes a file in the current directory for
every design unit.

   The file name of a design unit is build according to the unit.  For
an entity declaration, a package declaration or a configuration the file
name is `NAME.vhdl', where NAME is the name of the design unit.  For a
package body, the file name is `NAME-body.vhdl'.  Finally, for an
